                    "body": "Fair enough, but I'll defer to the R developers on that front.\r\n\r\nNote that while fsspec helps Python users, it's helpful to have the C++ filesystem implemented (not least to avoid constant calls back into Python, which also prevents the filesystem from truly implementing parallelism).\r\n\r\nInside {{open_dataset}} however you must have a filesystem. So from that angle I'm not sure how much this differs from the other issues.",
